Members of the National Assembly of Wales concerned that they ‘will be compared to Muppets’
There is an uproar among the Members of the National Assembly of Wales by a proposal that would change their title to MWP (Member of the Welsh Parliament - Member of the Welsh Parliament).
The proposal is a consequence of the plans to change the current name ‘Welsh Assembly’ to ‘Welsh Parliament’.
Members of the National Assembly of various political parties are concerned that the new name may seem ridiculous.
A member of the Labour Party's National Assembly of Wales said that MWP ‘ rhymes with Twp and Pwp'.
For readers outside Wales: twp is Welsh for fools and pwp is Welsh for poop.
A member of the National Assembly of Wales of the Plaid party said that the group as a whole is ‘disgruntled' and has proposed alternatives.
A member of the Welsh Conservative Party said his party is ‘open' for the name change, but notes that the words MWP and Muppet are very similar.
In this context, the Welsh letter W is pronounced a short u.
The Commission of the National Assembly of Wales, which is currently drafting legislation to implement the name change, said: ‘It is of course the members of the National Assembly of Wales themselves who are taking the final decision on their new title.'
With the Government of Wales Act 2017, the members of the National Assembly of Wales were given the right to change the name of the Assembly.
In June, the Commission published the results of a public consultation on the proposals, which showed that most people felt that the National Assembly should be renamed Parliament.
As regards the title of the members of the National Assembly, the Commission proposed ‘Welsh Parliament Members’ or WMPs, but the option MWP received the most support in the public consultation.
Currently, the members of the National Assembly would propose alternatives, but President Elin Jones will have a hard time reaching a consensus, and she will have to submit a bill on the changes in a few weeks' time.
The reform legislation also includes other changes to the way the National Assembly works, including rules on the suspension of members of the National Assembly and the structure of the system of committees.
Members of the National Assembly will finally be able to vote on their new title when they debate the legislation.
