The Secretary of State of North Korea told the United Nations on Saturday that the continued sanctions lead to increasing distrust in the United States and that under such circumstances the country could under no circumstances unilaterally abandon its nuclear weapons.
Ri Yong Ho told the U.N.'s annual General Assembly that over the past year North Korea had taken 'major goodwill measures', such as stopping nuclear and missile testing, dismantling the location for nuclear tests and promising not to spread nuclear weapons and nuclear technology.
