Ri referred to a joint statement by Kim Jong Un and Donald Trump at the very first summit between an active US president and a North Korean leader on June 12 in Singapore, when Kim promised to work towards the ‘denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula', while Trump promised guarantees of North Korea's security.
North Korea aims for a formal end to the Korea war of 1950-53, but the United States has said Pyongyang must first give up its nuclear weapons.
Washington has also opposed calls to ease the harsh international sanctions against North Korea.
"The US insists on ‘denuclearization first' and increases pressure through sanctions to achieve their goal in a compelling way and even by objecting to the ‘declaration of the end of war', said Ri.
‘The perception that sanctions can bring us to our knees is an air castle of the people who are ignorant of us.
